  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7021 sitting just below the max positive gamma strike at 7025 (28.3B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that level while providing strong support on dips given the PIN regime. The massive positive gamma wall at 7025 combined with secondary walls at 7000 and 7030 creates a tight trading range with dealers acting as liquidity providers in both directions. Watch for rejection at 7025 and potential mean reversion back toward 7000, with the GEX flip at 6860 remaining well out of range.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to chop between 7000-7025 with dealers capping upside moves.",
